Package: fsgeaGPU
Title: GPU-Accelerated Fast Gene Set Enrichment Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Martin", "Paliocha", email = "martin.paliocha@nmbu.no",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Gennady", "Korotkevich", role = "ctb",
           comment = "Original fgsea algorithm"),
    person("Alexey", "Sergushichev", role = "ctb",
           comment = "Original fgsea author"))
Description: A GPU/Torch-backed re-implementation of the fast gene set
    enrichment analysis algorithm of Korotkevich et al. (2021). The
    permutation null distribution and per-pathway enrichment scores are
    computed in batched tensor operations that run on CUDA, ROCm or
    Apple Metal devices via LibTorch, with a portable C++23
    'std::execution' CPU fallback. The R interface mirrors the public
    surface of the upstream 'fgsea' package, so existing pipelines can
    swap implementations by changing one import.
biocViews: GeneExpression, DifferentialExpression, GeneSetEnrichment, Pathways
Depends:
    R (>= 4.3)
Imports:
    Rcpp (>= 1.0.12),
    data.table,
    fastmatch,
    stats,
    utils
Suggests:
